parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, fires, and potentially life-threatening accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause a short circuit, leading to an engine compartment fire, which can result in a total loss of the vehicle and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: a fire begins in the engine compartment
a short circuit is detected in the engine electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Vehicle Movement Due to Transmission Shift Lever Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the driver is outside the vehicle or when the vehicle is on an incline.
symptoms: The transmission shift lever moves from park to reverse or other gears without driver input
the vehicle rolls backwards or forwards without warning
the vehicle starts to move on its own
the transmission jumps out of gear
the position indicator is vague or hard to read.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
The failure of the rack and pinion steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
The disconnection of the child seat can cause serious injury or ejection of the child from the vehicle, which can be fatal.
